cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR

The paper deals with image-to-image translation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). However, the specific application is in the medical field, specifically in hybrid X-ray and MR imaging (cs.MED). The paper also proposes modifications to the loss function to improve the generation of high-frequency details, which is a common problem in image generation and could be considered a contribution to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on improving the performance of the network could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
